data.description: **PRICE IMPROVEMENT** One word.....IMMACULATE, describes the condition of this gem.  Are you ready to live in your own tropical oasis?  This over the top, furnished two story pool home has the look and feel of a high-end resort.  Perfect opportunity for an Air B&B or a buyer who doesn't have the time to worry about shopping for furnishings and decor.  Located on the serene Coco Plum canal system which gives you access to fishing, kayaking & canoeing available right out your back door.  The lush tropical landscaping includes many mature palms and provides relaxing views while soaking up the rays in your very own lagoon style pool.  The in-ground spa is the perfect place to relax and enjoy that glass of wine from the built in kitchen wine/glass rack.  The spacious kitchen also includes all stainless steel appliances, extensive granite counterspace, and beautiful dark wood cabinets.  Three upstairs bedrooms, a loft and a ground floor office/den provide plenty of space for your family to spread out.  Primary retreat offers tranquility with a lighted tray ceiling and built in columns and arches with recessed lighting.  The primary bath is more like your home spa with two vanities, a water closet, a soaking tub and a walk in shower.  The whole house reverse osmosis system will ensure that you have the cleanest, freshest water available throughout the home.  Crown molding, rounded corners and arched doorways throughout the home give it the elegant touches that you deserve and dual zone A/C units let you cool the home where you need it the most.  Newer roof, pool heater and A/C unit.  Windows have been upgraded with impact in the front and shutters in the rear of the home.  The oversized 2 car garage is 580 sq ft and features epoxy flooring, lots of shelving/storage and a work bench, an extra refrigerator and freezer, updated breaker panel with generator connection and the 8400 Watt generator will stay with the house.  Located only 10 minutes from the Port Charlotte Town Center Mall makes shopping and dining out a breeze and the A rated elementary school up the street makes this home perfect for families with young children.  30 minutes from both Englewood and Venice Beaches so you can live like you are on vacation every day of the week.  No HOA or CDD fees and an X flood zone (which means flood insurance not required) will help you keep your monthly costs low.
